PATCH NOTES – MANDATORY STRUCTURE
────────────────────────────────
**Purpose:** To preserve total continuity between live sessions and prevent drift between fiction and record.

Each Patch Notes block must begin with: `=== SESSION PATCH NOTES [SESSION # — TITLE] ===`

**MANDATORY SECTIONS:**
• **NARRATIVE_SUMMARY** — What happened, in fiction (3-5 sentences)
• **UPDATED_LINES** — All mechanical changes (Karma, Nuyen, Condition, Gear, Reputation, Threads)
• **KARMA_AWARDED** — Total for session, with brief breakdown
• **FACTION ACTIVITY** — Including Competing Intelligences moves
• **THREAD_UPDATES** — Each active thread: [ACTION], [INTEL], or [RELATION] vector
• **TIMER_UPDATES** — Including Grace Period expirations
• **REPUTATION_IMPACT** — Street Cred, Notoriety, Public Awareness changes

**OPTIONAL BUT RECOMMENDED:**
• **NARRATIVE_MASS** — Tier (Minor/Major/Systemic) + tags if significant
• **PERSISTENT ADVANTAGES / DISADVANTAGES** — Updates only
• **SPARK_MOMENTS** — Seeds of legend, player or world surprises

**ALWAYS REQUIRED (Even if no other changes):**
• **NARRATIVE_SUMMARY**
• **WITNESS_LOG** (see AA4)

**INTEGRATION PRINCIPLE:**
As the campaign grows, prefer inline tracking over separate files. A contact's tags live with the contact. A thread's status lives with the thread. A threat's timer lives with the threat. The dossier is a web, not a stack.

────────────────────────────────
**TRACKING PA/PD & NARRATIVE MASS**
────────────────────────────────
If a Persistent Advantage/Disadvantage changed, or a significant Narrative Mass event occurred this session:
- **Add/Update** the PA/PD in Patch Notes under the relevant section.
- **For Narrative Mass:** Record Tier (Minor/Major/Systemic).
- **Optional Contextual Tags:** [LOYAL], [CRUEL], [SELFISH], [HONORABLE], [EXPEDIENT], or custom tags.
- **Mechanical Note:** Tags are primarily descriptive, shaping narrative interpretation. Mechanical effects may emerge when the fiction supports them, but tags alone do not grant automatic bonuses/penalties.
- **If no relevant change,** no entry is needed.
- **Grace Periods and Persistent Advantages are not rewards. They are causal integrity documentation.

